--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  1. Overview
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  phpTourney is a PHP script collection consisting of a simple user management,
  news, match reports and of course the tourney logic
  for single- and double-elimination brackets with or without qualification.
  It is released under the terms of the GPL. Have a look at LICENSE for details.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  2. Getting started
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

  2.1. Requirements
       - Apache Web Server
         (Tested: 2.2.16)
       - PHP
         (Tested: 5.3.3-7)
       - MySQL Server
         (Tested: 5.1.49-3)
       - Optional: ImageMagick
         (Tested: 6.6.0-4)

  2.2. Installation
       - Extract the phpTourney archive to a directory on your webserver
       - Make sure that the directories /data/screenshots and /data/serverlists
         and the file /VERSION are writable for the www-user
       - Execute the SQL-script /sql/phptourney.sql (i.e. with phpMyAdmin)
       - Copy the file /inc/config-default.inc.php to /inc/config.inc.php
         and edit its content to your needs
       - Log in with admin/password and create sections and seasons

  2.3. Update
       - To do an update just extract the new version over the old installation
         (don't forget to make backups first)
